  <description>
    <p>
      Chordcat is a desktop app that helps you identify and name chords based on inputted notes.
    </p>
    <p>
      Features:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Displays chord names when:
        <ul>
          <li>MIDI devices are connected and you play a chord</li>
          <li>Piano keys are clicked using the mouse</li>
          <li>The corresponding PC Keyboard keys are pressed</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Select MIDI device</li>
      <li>Inbuilt piano sounds</li>
      <li>Supports fullscreen mode and resizable window mode</li>
      <li>Includes 3 fun fonts (DejaVu Sans, Petaluma and FirstTimeWriting)</li>
    </ul>
  </description>

  <categories>
    <category>AudioVideo</category>
